---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Project Showcase - GigConnect">
  <section class="relative text-center py-24 bg-slate-900 text-white">
    <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold mb-6">
      GigConnect: Event Planning App Concept
    </h1>
    <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-slate-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
      A conceptual app designed to simplify event planning and artist bookings, created as my final project for CSCI E-12 Fundamentals of Web Application Development.
    </p>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-left space-y-10">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-2">Key Features</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-300 space-y-1">
          <li>Shortlist artists for events and manage schedules.</li>
          <li>Assign artists to stages with available time slots.</li>
          <li>Interactive visual planner to easily view event lineup.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-2">Tech Stack & Tools</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          Built with <strong>Astro</strong>, <strong>Tailwind CSS</strong>, and <strong>JavaScript</strong>.
        </p> 
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-2">Future Vision</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">
          Potential future features could include real-time collaboration, artist profiles with media galleries, 
          and integration with ticketing platforms.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
